Your project uses **MSTest v3 (3.8.0)** on **net8.0**. The latest is **MSTest v4 (4.1.0)**.

## Breaking changes that apply to your code

**`[ExpectedException]` removed** (lines 9, 16) — This is the main issue. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()` inside each test body:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

Same pattern for `Process_InvalidState_ThrowsInvalidOperation`.

## Other breaking changes (not in your code, but worth knowing)

| Change | Fix |
|---|---|
| `Assert.ThrowsException` removed | Use `Assert.ThrowsExactly` |
| `[TestMethod("name")]` constructor changed | Use `DisplayName = "name"` |
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed | Remove the enum argument |
| `TestContext.Properties.Contains` | Use `.ContainsKey()` |
| `TestTimeout.Infinite` removed | Use `int.MaxValue` |
| Custom `TestMethodAttribute.Execute` | Override `ExecuteAsync` instead |

## Key behavioral changes

- **`TreatDiscoveryWarningsAsErrors`** now defaults to `true`
- **`TestCase.Id`** generation changed — Azure DevOps test history may reset
- Analyzer severities upgraded (new warnings possible)

